  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACC Advancing Peace &amp; Democratic Reforms</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To advance the constitutional reforms of the local government system to address the winner-takes-all system (WTA) of government which currently pertains in Ghana, and which has caused an exclusionary form of politics that has bred electoral and vigilante violence. The project objectives are as follows: a. To facilitate endorsement of the proposed reforms by national stakeholders who opposed the 2019 CA and build their ownership of a national conference on the reforms. b. To contribute to the organization of a national conference on the reforms in April 2022, marking the 30th Anniversary of the 1992 Constitution. c. To educate the public on the proposed reforms and the solutions to marginalization and political violence that the reforms will accrue.</narrative>
  </description>
